description.narrative: The Danish-Arab Partnership Program is Denmark#s collaboration program with the Middle East and North Africa. The program helps to strengthen good governance and ensure economic opportunities, especially for young people and women in the region, through partnerships. Countries of focus are Morocco, Tunisia, Egypt and Jordan. Since 2003, Denmark has strengthened its efforts in the Middle East and North Africa as part of the general Danish foreign and development policy. The project in Tunisia will focuson building capacityof 5 local partners every year to reach 1200 employed young Tunisians by 2022 in the following sectors: Agriculture Craft Construction
